#=======================================================================
#
# README
#
# The script to do failure analysis is mfg_parse.pl
# The bash script mfg_parse.sh copies logs from /mfg_log/
# on MFG server (192.168.3.2) and calls mfg_parse.pl and convert.pl
# The script convert.pl converts the yaml format output of mfg_parse.pl
# to a spreadsheet
# 
# 1. Copy the latest mfg_parse.sh to /home/mfg/mfg_diag_fa/
# directory on MFG server
# 2. Copy the latest mfg_parse.pl and convert.pl to /home/mfg/mfg_diag_fa/scripts/
# directory on MFG server
# 3. Then in /home/mfg/mfg_diag_fa/, put all the SNs that need
# parsing into a file, one SN per line
# 4. Run the mfg_parse.sh script with the syntax below:
#    Usage: ./mfg_parse.sh [options]
#    options:
#    -c, --card        Card type
#    -s, --stage       Stage(s), comma separated
#    -f, --faopt       FA option: first/last/all/first_run/last_run/all_run
#    -l, --snfile      SN file
#    -d, --dlogdir     Directory to store logs
#    -e, --slogdir     Directory where original logs are stored
#    -r, --remote      Mfg logs are stored remotely
#    -k, --keep        Keep extracted logs after running parser
#    -t, --testname    Test name (optional parameter to only parse this particular test name)
#    -m, --mfgerrcode  Mfg err code (optional parameter to only parse this particular MFG err code)
#    -h, --help        Print this help

#    Example:
#    ./mfg_parse.sh -c ORTANO2 -s 4c-h -f last -l ./sn_list.txt -d debug
# 5. The output is parse_rersult_<stage>_<timestamp>.xlsx in the same directory
#=======================================================================

